# Function to generate DCE choice tasks from an experimental design matrix
generate_dce_tasks_from_design <- function(design_matrix, dce_attributes, dce_levels, num_tasks, num_alternatives_per_task, status_quo_values) {
  
  dce_choice_tasks <- list()
  
  for (i in 1:num_tasks) {
    start_row <- (i - 1) * num_alternatives_per_task + 1
    end_row <- start_row + num_alternatives_per_task - 1
    
    task_design_data <- design_matrix[start_row:end_row, ]
    
    # CRITICAL: Ensure the initial dataframe structure has 6 rows (6 attributes)
    current_task_df <- data.frame(attribute = dce_attributes, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
    
    for (j in 1:num_alternatives_per_task) {
      prog_name <- paste0("Circular Microgrid-", j)
      prog_levels <- c()
      
      # Loop through all 6 attributes
      for (k in 1:length(dce_attributes)) {
        attribute_name <- names(dce_levels)[k]
        level_index <- task_design_data[j, attribute_name]
        
        # ðŸ›‘ CRITICAL FIX: Handle Ngene Index 0 ðŸ›‘
        if (level_index == 0) {
          # If Ngene used index 0, substitute the Status Quo value for this attribute.
          # The status_quo_values vector must be indexed correctly (1 to 6)
          prog_levels <- c(prog_levels, status_quo_values[k])
        } else {
          # Use the 1-based index directly
          prog_levels <- c(prog_levels, dce_levels[[attribute_name]][level_index])
        }
      }
      current_task_df[[prog_name]] <- prog_levels
    }
    
    current_task_df[["No Circular Microgrid"]] <- status_quo_values
    
    dce_choice_tasks[[i]] <- current_task_df
  }
  
  return(dce_choice_tasks)
}

server <- function(input, output, session) {
  
  
  # =======================================================
  # 1. REACTIVE VALUES AND INITIAL SETUP (SHINYLIVE READY)
  # =======================================================
  
  # Reactive values for survey flow and data storage
  user_group <- reactiveVal(sample(c("control", "neutral", "honesty"), 1))
  survey_data_collector <- reactiveVal(list())
  dce_tasks_to_use <- reactiveVal(NULL) 
  
  show_dce_intro_page <- reactiveVal(TRUE)
  show_sq_only_question <- reactiveVal(FALSE)
  nav_ready <- reactiveVal(FALSE)
  
  current_demo_page <- reactiveVal(1) 
  current_energy_page <- reactiveVal(1)
  show_scramble_intro <- reactiveVal(TRUE)
  current_scramble_page <- reactiveVal(1)
  current_table <- reactiveVal(1) 
  current_dce_task <- reactiveVal(1) 
  
  # Define the chunks for the attitude tables
  table_chunks <- list(
    1:8,   # Table 1: 8 items
    9:16,  # Table 2: 8 items
    17:24, # Table 3: 8 items
    25:33  # Table 4: 9 items
  )
  
  # UI Bridge for the Status Quo question
  output$sq_only_condition <- renderText({
    as.character(tolower(show_sq_only_question()))
  })
  outputOptions(output, 'sq_only_condition', suspendWhenHidden = FALSE)
  
  # NOTE: Local auto-save and PROGRESS_DIR logic removed. 
  # This prevents crashes on tablets where browsers are sandboxed.
  
  # --- Group-based tab control ---
  observeEvent(user_group(), {
    if (user_group() == "control") {
      hide(selector = "#main_navbar a[data-value='scrambled_exercise']")
    } else {
      show(selector = "#main_navbar a[data-value='scrambled_exercise']")
    }
  }, ignoreNULL = FALSE)
  
  # Action for "Start Survey" button
  observeEvent(input$start_survey, {
    enable(selector = "#main_navbar a[data-value='page_enumerator_info']")
    updateNavbarPage(session, "main_navbar", selected = "page_enumerator_info")
    
    current_data <- survey_data_collector()
    current_data$group <- user_group() 
    current_data$start_timestamp <- as.character(Sys.time())
    survey_data_collector(current_data)
  })
  
  # =======================================================
  # 2. ENUMERATOR INFO & LOCATION LOGIC
  # =======================================================
  
  observeEvent(input$city_village, {
    req(input$city_village != "")
    region_type_value <- location_data %>%
      filter(Location == input$city_village) %>%
      pull(Region_type) %>% as.character()
    
    updateTextInput(session, "loc_type", value = region_type_value[1])
    
    if (region_type_value[1] == "Urban") {
      dce_tasks_to_use(dce_choice_tasks_urban)
    } else {
      dce_tasks_to_use(dce_choice_tasks_rural)
    }
  })
  
  observeEvent(input$submit_enumerator_info, {
    if (is.null(input$city_village) || input$city_village == "" || is.na(input$enumerator_id)) {
      showModal(modalDialog(title = "Incomplete", "Please fill in all details."))
    } else {
      current_data <- survey_data_collector()
      current_data$city_village <- input$city_village
      current_data$enumerator_id <- input$enumerator_id
      current_data$loc_type <- input$loc_type
      current_data$enumerator_info_end_time <- as.character(Sys.time())
      survey_data_collector(current_data)
      
      if (user_group() == "control") {
        enable(selector = "#main_navbar a[data-value='dce_section']")
        updateNavbarPage(session, "main_navbar", selected = "dce_section")
      } else {
        enable(selector = "#main_navbar a[data-value='scrambled_exercise']")
        updateNavbarPage(session, "main_navbar", selected = "scrambled_exercise")
      }
    }
  })
  
  
  # =======================================================
  # 2. UI RENDERERS AND DYNAMIC OUTPUTS (Ordered by Tab)
  # =======================================================
  
  # --- Energy Consumption Tab Outputs ---
  
  # Server for Q4: Frequency of appliance use (Table-like layout)
  output$q4_appliance_freq_ui <- renderUI({
    appliance_col_width <- 3
    choice_col_widths <- c(1, 2, 1, 2, 1, 2) # Sums to 9
    
    tagList(
      # Header row
      fluidRow(class = "table-row-header",
               column(appliance_col_width, class = "col-appliance", tags$b("Appliance")), # Appliance name header
               # Columns for each frequency choice
               lapply(seq_along(freq_choices), function(i) {
                 column(choice_col_widths[i], tags$b(freq_choices[i]))
               })
      ),
      # Data rows for each appliance

    current_energy_page(3)
  })
  
  
  # Observer 3: Submitting Page 3 (Q4: Appliance Time of Day Table)
  observeEvent(input$next_energy_3, { # <-- REQUIRED START
    
    # --- 1. Validation for Page 3 (Q4: Time of Day Table) ---
    for (app in appliances) {
      selected_count <- 0
      
      # Loop over the sanitized values (time_choice_values) used for input IDs
      for (safe_value in time_choice_values) {
        input_id <- paste0("time_", gsub(" ", "_", app), "_", safe_value)
        
        # Check if the checkbox exists (not NULL) AND is TRUE
        if (!is.null(input[[input_id]]) && input[[input_id]] == TRUE) {
          selected_count <- selected_count + 1
        }
      }
      
      if (selected_count == 0) {
        showModal(modalDialog(title = "Incomplete", paste0("Please make at least one selection for '", app, "' in Question 4 (Time of Day Used).")))
        return()
      }
    }
    
    # 2. Store Page 3 data and Timestamp
    
    # Read data ONCE
    current_data <- survey_data_collector()
    
    # Store Q4 data (Time of Day)
    for (app in appliances) { # <-- Start of outer storage loop
      app_clean <- gsub(" ", "_", app)
      selected_times <- c()
      
      # Inner loop uses sanitized values to correctly lookup input IDs
      for (safe_value in time_choice_values) {
        input_id <- paste0("time_", app_clean, "_", safe_value)
        if (!is.null(input[[input_id]]) && input[[input_id]] == TRUE) {
          # Store the label corresponding to the safe value
          label_index <- which(time_choice_values == safe_value)
          selected_times <- c(selected_times, time_choice_labels[label_index])
        }
      }
      # Update the reactive list with the collected labels for this appliance
      current_data[[paste0("time_", app_clean)]] <- paste(selected_times, collapse = "; ") %||% NA_character_
    } # <-- End of outer storage loop
    
    # Store final page timestamp
    current_data$energy_page_3_end_time <- as.character(Sys.time())
    survey_data_collector(current_data)
    
    # 3. Navigate: Page 3 -> Page 4 (Q5-Q7)
    shinyjs::hide("energy_page_3")
    shinyjs::show("energy_page_4")
    current_energy_page(4)
    
  }) # <-- REQUIRED CLOSING BRACE AND PARENTHESIS FOR observeEvent
  
  
  # Observer 4: Submitting Page 4 (Q5-7: elec_access, sufficient_elec + cond, willing_alt_energy)
  observeEvent(input$next_energy_4, {
    # 1. Validation for Page 4 (Q5, Q6, Q7)
    if (is.null(input$elec_access) || is.null(input$sufficient_elec) || is.null(input$willing_alt_energy)) {
      showModal(modalDialog(title = "Incomplete", "Please answer all questions on Page 4 (Q5, Q6, Q7)."))
      return()
    }
    
    # ðŸ›‘ Validate Conditional Sub-questions (6b & 6c)
    if (input$sufficient_elec == "No" && 
        (is.null(input$week_outage_freq) || is.null(input$daily_outage_freq))) {
      showModal(modalDialog(title = "Incomplete", "Please answer both conditional sub-questions (6b and 6c) since you answered 'No' to Q6."))
      return()
    }
    
    #Store Timestamp
    current_data <- survey_data_collector()
    current_data$energy_page_4_end_time <- as.character(Sys.time())
    
    # 2. Store Page 4 data (including conditional questions)
    current_data <- survey_data_collector()
    current_data$elec_access <- input$elec_access %||% NA_character_
    current_data$sufficient_elec <- input$sufficient_elec %||% NA_character_
    current_data$willing_alt_energy <- input$willing_alt_energy %||% NA_character_
    
    # Store conditional Q6b and Q6c
    current_data$week_outage_freq <- if (input$sufficient_elec == "No") {
      input$week_outage_freq %||% NA_character_
    } else {
      NA_character_
    }
    current_data$daily_outage_freq <- if (input$sufficient_elec == "No") {
      input$daily_outage_freq %||% NA_character_
    } else {
      NA_character_
    }
    current_data$energy_page_4_end_time <- as.character(Sys.time())
    survey_data_collector(current_data)
    
    # 3. Navigate: Page 4 -> Page 5 (Q8-Q13)
    shinyjs::hide("energy_page_4")
    shinyjs::show("energy_page_5")
    current_energy_page(5)
  })
  
  
  # Observer 5: Final Energy Submission (Q8-11: access_microgrid + cond, energy_spend, satisfaction, comm_view_re_rel)
  observeEvent(input$submit_energy_consumption, { 
    # 1. Validation for Page 5 (Q8-Q11)
    if (is.null(input$access_microgrid) || is.null(input$energy_spend) || 
        is.null(input$satisfaction) || is.null(input$comm_view_re_rel) || is.null(input$beh_qual_check)) {
      showModal(modalDialog(title = "Incomplete", "Please answer all questions on Page 5 (Q8-Q13)."))
      return()
    }
    
    # Validate Conditional Sub-question (8b)
    if (input$access_microgrid == "Yes" && is.na(input$microgrid_hours)) { 
      showModal(modalDialog(title = "Incomplete", "Please answer conditional sub-question (8b) since you answered 'Yes' to Q8."))
      return()
    }
    
    # Check if the conditional question was visible (i.e., if National Grid was selected in Q3.1 or Q3.2)
    if ("Electricity (National Grid)" %in% input$primary_energy || 
        "Electricity (National Grid)" %in% input$other_energy) {
      
      if (is.null(input$elec_band) || input$elec_band == "") {
        showModal(modalDialog(title = "Incomplete", "Please select your electricity tariff band.", easyClose = TRUE))
        return()
      }
    }
    
    #Store Timestamp
    current_data <- survey_data_collector()
    current_data$energy_page_5_end_time <- as.character(Sys.time())
    
    # 2. Store Page 5 data and finalize Energy Consumption storage
    current_data <- survey_data_collector()
    current_data$access_microgrid <- input$access_microgrid %||% NA_character_
    
    # Store conditional Q8b
    current_data$microgrid_hours <- if (input$access_microgrid == "Yes") {
      input$microgrid_hours %||% NA_integer_
    } else {
      NA_integer_
    }
    current_data$energy_spend <- input$energy_spend %||% NA_character_
    current_data$elec_band <- if ("Electricity (National Grid)" %in% input$primary_energy || 
                                  "Electricity (National Grid)" %in% input$other_energy) {
      input$elec_band %||% NA_character_
    } else {
      NA_character_
    }
    current_data$satisfaction <- input$satisfaction %||% NA_character_
    current_data$comm_view_re_rel <- input$comm_view_re_rel %||% NA_character_
    current_data$beh_qual_check <- paste(input$beh_qual_check, collapse = "; ") %||% NA_character_
    current_data$energy_page_5_end_time <- as.character(Sys.time())
    survey_data_collector(current_data)
    
    # 3. Conditional Navigation to the next full tab (Scrambled or DCE)
    # Navigation is now to Demographics
    enable(selector = "#main_navbar a[data-value='demographics']")
    updateNavbarPage(session, "main_navbar", selected = "demographics")

  })
  
  # --- 4. Scrambled Sentences Flow Control (Intro to Tasks) ---
  
  observeEvent(input$start_scramble_flow, {
    
    #Store intro timestamp
    current_data <- survey_data_collector()
    current_data$scramble_intro_end_time <- as.character(Sys.time())
    survey_data_collector(current_data)
    
    # Hide the intro and show the first sentence
    show_scramble_intro(FALSE) 
    current_scramble_page(1) # Ensure we start at Sentence 1
    
    # The UI will automatically render the content of output$scrambled_sentences
  })
  
  # --- 4. Scrambled Sentences Paging (Internal) ---
  observeEvent(input$next_scramble_sentence, {
    current_index <- current_scramble_page()
    input_id <- paste0("scramble_", current_index)
    
    # 1. Validation Check
    if (is.null(input[[input_id]]) || nchar(trimws(input[[input_id]])) == 0) {
      showModal(modalDialog(
        title = "Incomplete Sentence",
        "Please complete the current sentence before moving to the next.",
        easyClose = TRUE
      ))
      return()
    }
    
    # 2. Store Data and Time (All in one block)
    current_data <- survey_data_collector()
    
    # Store Timestamp (Time the user clicked 'Next')
    current_data[[paste0("scramble_sentence_", current_index, "_end_time")]] <- as.character(Sys.time())
    
    # Store Sentence Text
    current_data[[input_id]] <- input[[input_id]]
    
    survey_data_collector(current_data) # Save changes once
    
    # 3. Advance to Next Sentence
    current_scramble_page(current_index + 1)
  })
  
  # --- 4. Scrambled Sentences Submission (Final Page) ---
  observeEvent(input$submit_scrambled_sentences, {
    final_index <- 10 # This is the index of the final sentence
    input_id <- paste0("scramble_", final_index)
    
    # 1. Validation Check for Final Sentence
    if (is.null(input[[input_id]]) || nchar(trimws(input[[input_id]])) == 0) {
      showModal(modalDialog(
        title = "Incomplete Section",
        "Please complete the final scrambled sentence before proceeding.",
        easyClose = TRUE
      ))
      return()
    }
    
    # 2. Store Data and Time (All in one block)
    current_data <- survey_data_collector()
    
    # Store Timestamp (Time the user clicked 'Submit')
    current_data[[paste0("scramble_sentence_", final_index, "_end_time")]] <- as.character(Sys.time())
    
    # Store Sentence Text
    current_data[[input_id]] <- input[[input_id]]
    
    # Capture overall section end time (optional, but good for total time calc)
    current_data$scramble_section_end_time <- as.character(Sys.time())
    
    # Ensure all 10 scramble columns exist (as before)
    for (i in 1:10) {
      col_name <- paste0("scramble_", i)
      if (!col_name %in% names(current_data)) {
        current_data[[col_name]] <- NA_character_
      }
    }
    
    survey_data_collector(current_data)
    
    # 3. Navigate to the next section (DCE)
    enable(selector = "#main_navbar a[data-value='dce_section']")
    updateNavbarPage(session, "main_navbar", selected = "dce_section")
  })
  
  # --- 5. DCE Section Flow Control (Consumer Opinions - 1) ---
  
  # Reactive to track if all DCE tasks are "No Circular Microgrid"
  show_sq_only_question <- reactiveVal(FALSE)
  
  # --- 5.1 Start DCE flow after intro button click ---
  observeEvent(input$start_dce_flow, {
    
    # Store Timestamp for DCE Intro 
    current_data <- survey_data_collector()
    current_data$dce_intro_end_time <- as.character(Sys.time())
    survey_data_collector(current_data)
    
    # Hide intro and show first choice task
    show_dce_intro_page(FALSE)
    current_dce_task(1)
    shinyjs::show("choicetask1")
    lapply(2:8, function(i) shinyjs::hide(paste0("choicetask", i)))
    shinyjs::hide("dce_submit") # Submit hidden until all tasks answered
  })
  
  # --- 5.2 Navigation & storage for each DCE task ---
  lapply(1:8, function(i) {
    observeEvent(input[[paste0("click2choice", i)]], {
      selected_choice <- input[[paste0("dce_selected_task_", i)]]
      
      if (is.null(selected_choice) || selected_choice == "") {
        showModal(modalDialog(
          title = "Incomplete",
          paste0("Please make a selection for Choice Task ", i),
          easyClose = TRUE
        ))
        return()
      }
      
      # Store choice and timestamp
      current_data <- survey_data_collector()
      current_data[[paste0("dce_", i)]] <- selected_choice
      current_data[[paste0("dce_task_", i, "_end_time")]] <- as.character(Sys.time())
      survey_data_collector(current_data)
      
      # Hide current task
      shinyjs::hide(paste0("choicetask", i))
      
      # Advance to next task
      next_task_idx <- current_dce_task() + 1
      current_dce_task(next_task_idx)
      
      if (next_task_idx <= 8) {
        shinyjs::show(paste0("choicetask", next_task_idx))
      } else {
        # ðŸ›‘ CRITICAL FIX ðŸ›‘
        # Check the condition and set the flag IMMEDIATELY after task 8 is stored.
        
        all_sq_chosen <- TRUE
        current_data <- survey_data_collector() 
        
        for (j in 1:8) {
          if (current_data[[paste0("dce_", j)]] != "No Circular Microgrid") {
            all_sq_chosen <- FALSE
            break
          }
        }
        
        if (all_sq_chosen) {
          # Set flag to TRUE to make the question visible immediately.
          show_sq_only_question(TRUE)
        }
        
        # Show submit div after last task
        shinyjs::show("dce_submit")
      }
    })
  })
  
  # --- 5.3 Final DCE submission ---
  observeEvent(input$submit_dce, {
    
    # 1. Mandatory Validation Check (Check if the conditional question, if visible, was answered)
    
    # Use the flag's current state to decide if validation is necessary
    question_is_required <- show_sq_only_question()
    
    if (question_is_required && (is.null(input$sq_only_choice) || input$sq_only_choice == "")) {
      showModal(modalDialog(title = "Incomplete", "Please answer the follow-up question (Q9) before proceeding."))
      return()
    }
    
    # 2. STORE CONDITIONAL QUESTION DATA AND FINAL TIMESTAMP
    current_data <- survey_data_collector()
    
    # Store the value (it will be NA if the question was hidden/not required)
    current_data$sq_only_choice <- input$sq_only_choice %||% NA_character_
    current_data$dce_section_end_time <- as.character(Sys.time())
    
    survey_data_collector(current_data)
    
    # 3. NAVIGATION
    # Navigation is now to Attitudes
    enable(selector = "#main_navbar a[data-value='attitude_questions']")
    updateNavbarPage(session, "main_navbar", selected = "attitude_questions")
  })
  
  # --- 6. Awareness Workshop Submission ---
  observeEvent(input$submit_awareness, {
    
    # Validation Check
    if (is.null(input$willing_attend_workshop) || input$willing_attend_workshop == "" ||
        is.null(input$primary_energy_awareness_repeat) || input$primary_energy_awareness_repeat == "") {
      showModal(modalDialog(
        title = "Incomplete Section",
        "Please answer all questions in the Awareness Workshop section before proceeding.",
        easyClose = TRUE
      ))
      return()
    }
    
    # 1. Read data ONCE
    current_data <- survey_data_collector() 
    
    # 2. Store Timestamp
    current_data$awareness_workshop_end_time <- as.character(Sys.time())
    
    # 3. Store Awareness Data (using the same current_data variable)
    current_data$willing_attend_workshop <- input$willing_attend_workshop %||% NA_character_
    current_data$primary_energy_awareness_repeat <- input$primary_energy_awareness_repeat %||% NA_character_
    survey_data_collector(current_data) # Update reactive value ONCE
    
    # Navigation
    # Navigation is to Final Opinions
    enable(selector = "#main_navbar a[data-value='opinions4']") 
    updateNavbarPage(session, "main_navbar", selected = "opinions4") 
  })
  
  # --- 7. Attitudes Flow Control (Consumer Opinions - 3) ---
  # Observer for the "Next" button (Tables 1, 2, and 3)
  observeEvent(input$next_table, {
    
    # ðŸ›‘ START OF MISSING VALIDATION BLOCK ðŸ›‘
    current_table_indices <- table_chunks[[current_table()]]
    all_answered <- TRUE # Initialize the variable that was 'not found'
    
    for (i in current_table_indices) {
      if (is.null(input[[paste0("attitude_q_", i)]])) {
        all_answered <- FALSE
        break
      }
    }
    # ðŸ›‘ END OF MISSING VALIDATION BLOCK ðŸ›‘
    
    if (all_answered) {
      # 1. Read data ONCE
      current_data <- survey_data_collector() 
      
      # 2. Store Timestamp for the table being left
      current_data[[paste0("attitudes_table_", current_table(), "_end_time")]] <- as.character(Sys.time())
      
      # 3. Store data for Tables 1, 2, or 3 (using the same current_data variable)
      # current_table_indices is now correctly available
      for (i in current_table_indices) {
        current_data[[paste0("att_", i)]] <- as.integer(input[[paste0("attitude_q_", i)]]) %||% NA_integer_ 
      }
      survey_data_collector(current_data) # Update reactive value ONCE
      
      if (current_table() < 4) {
        current_table(current_table() + 1)
      }
    } else {
      showModal(modalDialog(
        title = "Incomplete Section",
        "Please select an option for each statement before proceeding.",
        easyClose = TRUE,
        footer = NULL
      ))
    }
  })
  
  # Observer for the "Next Section" button (Table 4 Exit)
  observeEvent(input$next_to_opinions4, {
    
    # ðŸ›‘ START OF MISSING VALIDATION BLOCK ðŸ›‘
    current_table_indices <- table_chunks[[4]] # Indices for the 4th table
    all_answered <- TRUE # Initialize the variable that was 'not found'
    
    for (i in current_table_indices) {
      if (is.null(input[[paste0("attitude_q_", i)]])) {
        all_answered <- FALSE
        break
      }
    }
    # ðŸ›‘ END OF MISSING VALIDATION BLOCK ðŸ›‘
    
    # 1. Check if all questions were answered (Must use the newly defined 'all_answered')
    if (!all_answered) {
      showModal(modalDialog(
        title = "Incomplete Section",
        "Please select an option for each statement in this final attitude section before proceeding.",
        easyClose = TRUE,
        footer = NULL
      ))
      return()
    }
    
    # Store Timestamp for the final table (Table 4)
    current_data <- survey_data_collector()
    current_data$attitudes_table_4_end_time <- as.character(Sys.time())
    
    # 2. Store the data for the 4th (final) attitude table
    for (i in current_table_indices) { 
      # Note: You still need to fix the typo here if it still exists from before:
      # It should be [[paste0("att_", i)]] NOT [[paste0("att_", i)]]]
      current_data[[paste0("att_", i)]] <- as.integer(input[[paste0("attitude_q_", i)]]) %||% NA_integer_
    }
    survey_data_collector(current_data)
    
    # 3. Navigate to the final tab
    # Navigation is now to Household Energy Consumption
    enable(selector = "#main_navbar a[data-value='energy_consumption']")
    updateNavbarPage(session, "main_navbar", selected = "energy_consumption")
  })
  
  # --- 8. Final Submission: Consumer Opinions - 4 (Shinylive Compatible) ---
  output$next_opinions4 <- downloadHandler(
    filename = function() {
      # Creates a unique filename for the tablet's Downloads folder
      paste0("Survey_Enum", input$enumerator_id, "_", format(Sys.time(), "%Y%m%d_%H%M"), ".csv")
    },
    content = function(file) {
      
      # --- 1. VALIDATION CHECK ---
      required_radio_inputs <- c("gov_pol_aware", "reswitch_incentive", "rep_benefit")
      valid_main <- all(sapply(required_radio_inputs, function(x) {
        !is.null(input[[x]]) && input[[x]] != ""
      }))
      
      valid_conditional_comms <- TRUE
      if (!is.null(input$gov_pol_aware) && input$gov_pol_aware == "Yes") {
        if (is.null(input$comms_channels) || input$comms_channels == "") {
          valid_conditional_comms <- FALSE
        }
      }
      
      if (!valid_main || !valid_conditional_comms) {
        showModal(modalDialog(
          title = "Incomplete Section",
          "Please ensure you answer all required questions in this final section before saving.",
          easyClose = TRUE
        ))
        return()
      }
      
      # --- 2. FINAL DATA COLLECTION ---
      current_data <- survey_data_collector()
      
      # Store Timestamp and final metadata
      current_data$final_opinions_end_time <- as.character(Sys.time())
      current_data$end_timestamp <- as.character(Sys.time())
      
      # Map all UI inputs to the data list
      current_data$gov_pol_aware      <- input$gov_pol_aware %||% NA_character_
      current_data$reswitch_incentive <- input$reswitch_incentive %||% NA_character_
      current_data$rep_benefit        <- input$rep_benefit %||% NA_character_
      current_data$comms_channels     <- if (!is.null(input$gov_pol_aware) && input$gov_pol_aware == "Yes") input$comms_channels else NA_character_
      current_data$rep_exp            <- if (!is.null(input$rep_benefit) && input$rep_benefit == "Yes") input$rep_exp else NA_character_
      current_data$add_info_ret       <- input$add_info_ret %||% "" 
      
      # Define all columns expected in the final CSV
      all_columns <- c(
        "group", "start_timestamp", "end_timestamp",
        "city_village", "enumerator_id", "loc_type", "age", "gender", "ethnicity", "education",
        "employment_type", "household_size", "num_children", "income_range", "hh", "hhownership",
        "primary_energy", "other_energy", "elec_access", "sufficient_elec", "week_outage_freq", "daily_outage_freq",
        "willing_alt_energy", "access_microgrid", "microgrid_hours", "energy_spend","elec_band", "satisfaction", "comm_view_re_rel","beh_qual_check",
        "willing_attend_workshop", "primary_energy_awareness_repeat",
        paste0("freq_", gsub(" ", "_", appliances)),
        paste0("time_", gsub(" ", "_", appliances)),
        paste0("scramble_", 1:10),
        paste0("att_", 1:33),
        paste0("dce_", 1:8),
        "sq_only_choice",
        "gov_pol_aware", "reswitch_incentive", "rep_benefit", "comms_channels", "rep_exp", "add_info_ret",
        "enumerator_info_end_time", "demo_page_1_end_time", "demo_page_2_end_time", "demo_page_3_end_time", 
        "energy_page_1_end_time", "energy_page_2_end_time", "energy_page_3_end_time", "energy_page_4_end_time", "energy_page_5_end_time", 
        paste0("scramble_sentence_", 1:10, "_end_time"), paste0("dce_task_", 1:8, "_end_time"), 
        "dce_section_end_time", "awareness_workshop_end_time", 
        "attitudes_table_1_end_time", "attitudes_table_2_end_time", "attitudes_table_3_end_time", "attitudes_table_4_end_time", "final_opinions_end_time"
      )
      
      # Ensure every column exists to avoid errors
      for (col_name in all_columns) {
        if (!col_name %in% names(current_data)) {
          current_data[[col_name]] <- NA_character_
        }
      }
      
      # --- 3. EXPORT TO CSV ---
      final_data_tibble <- as_tibble(current_data[all_columns])
      write.csv(final_data_tibble, file, row.names = FALSE)
      
      # --- 4. SUCCESS UI ---
      showModal(modalDialog(
        title = "Survey Complete & Data Saved!",
        "Thank you! Your survey response has been saved to the 'Downloads' folder of this tablet. You can now close the survey.",
        footer = NULL,
        easyClose = FALSE
      ))
      
      # Disable the navbar to prevent further editing
      disable("main_navbar")
    
    },
    # ADD THIS LINE:
    contentType = "text/csv"
    )
}
